    "description": "Kanseki Co., Ltd. manages home centers, specialty stores, and related business in Japan. The company operates pet stores that offer a range of dogs, cats, birds and other animals, goldfishes, tropical fishes, and breeding equipment. It also operates supermarkets that include seasonings, canned foods, beverages, livestock processed goods, miscellaneous goods, and frozen food products; and off house stores that offer furniture, home appliances, interior goods, gifts, household goods, clothing, sporting goods, etc. In addition, the company operates Wildburn, a hamburger and pasta shop. The company was formerly known as Hattori Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Kanseki Co., Ltd. in December 1975. The company was incorporated in 1975 and is headquartered in Utsunomiya, Japan."
